snippet: U.S. Senator Dianne Feinstein, chair of the Senate Select Committee on Intelligence, said recent "lone wolf" terrorism attacks show that propaganda from groups like Islamic State are inspiring attacks on U.S. soil....

headline.print_headline: Violent Islamist Propaganda Inspiring Attacks in U.S.: Senator Feinstein
headline.main: Violent Islamist Propaganda Inspiring Attacks in U.S.: Senator Feinstein

lead_paragraph: U.S. Senator Dianne Feinstein, chair of the Senate Select Committee on Intelligence, said recent "lone wolf" terrorism attacks show that propaganda from groups like Islamic State are inspiring attacks on U.S. soil.
